parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility during rainy or snowy conditions, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Windshield wipers work sporadically
stop working suddenly
or fail to stop at all
windshield wipers only work sometimes
windshield washer does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable brake behavior can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes suddenly fail or have reduced effectiveness
the ABS system engages unnecessarily
causing longer stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning ABS system can cause the brakes to engage unnecessarily, leading to longer stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system engages at low speeds
the ABS system overrides the normal braking system
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds. Additionally, it can cause the vehicle to shut down, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls unexpectedly
the vehicle shuts down
the fuel gauge gives incorrect readings
the fuel pump fails to supply fuel to the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank wiring harness can cause a short circuit, which can lead to a fire, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The fuel tank wiring harness is frayed or damaged
the fuel pump plug is damaged
the vehicle experiences electrical issues.
